 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P02-T014 (Registry compiler + deterministic output)
+
+- Fourteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S1-P02), one task per run. Goal: from one source generate the runtime, UI labels, D1 seed, health and backfill plan. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; the seed is a compiled artifact and is NOT applied to production D1. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/compile_registry.py (the compiler, which first runs the T012 validator plus hard checks, then emits deterministic outputs) and compiled/{runtime.json, ui_labels.json, seed.sql, registry_hash.txt}. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P02-T014/test-results/compile_tests.txt): two consecutive compiles of source_registry.json are byte-identical (registry_hash sha256:d63cf6bd4d72...e7fb; outputs sorted by source_id with sorted keys and no timestamps); and the compiler FAILS on a duplicate source_id, a non-boolean enabled, and an unknown authority_kind. This puts the mechanism to eliminate multiple source truths in place (T013 recorded the migration; T014 generates runtime/UI/seed from the one Registry), and the registry_hash anchors the T015 source drift CI. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 rows 0 (seed not applied), R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P02-T013 (migrate live sources into the Registry)
 
 - Thirteenth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S1-P02), one task per run. Goal: eliminate the multiple source truths (YAML, Worker, D1, UI) WITHOUT changing existing crawl behaviour. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; docs/data migration only -- no worker/config/D1 change. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: source_registry.json (33 registry rows migrated from the live truth, worker_cloud.js REGISTRY, conforming to the T012 schema), SOURCE_MIGRATION_MAPPING.csv (33 rows, worker id -> registry source_id, 1:1 id-preserving, worker REGISTRY = source of truth), SOURCE_LEGACY_EXCEPTIONS.md (EXC-1 board3 media mislabeled '官方' -> media/official_evidence=false per DRIFT-FACT-006/FACT-003; EXC-2 config vs worker board3 divergence; EXC-3 aggregator/discovery non-official). Acceptance verified: benchmarks/before.json (worker source set) == benchmarks/after.json (registry source set) -- identical source_id set and per-board membership, so crawl behaviour is unchanged; each live source_id is unique (33 unique); and the migrated registry validates VALID against the T012 schema (media are official_evidence=false; no illegal china_official level). Classification: preprint 3, journal 17, media 4, intl_official 8, aggregator 1; official_evidence true 28 / false 5. The worker/D1/UI still hold their own copies -- unifying them via a compiler is T014, and the source drift CI is T015. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
